{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id62701036-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s1660d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1660d"},"text":"§ 1660d.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Conferring with urban Indian organizations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id62701037-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s1660d/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definition of confer","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this section, the term “confer” means to engage in an open and free exchange of information and opinions that—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id62701038-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s1660d/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" leads to mutual understanding and comprehension; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id62701039-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s1660d/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" emphasizes trust, respect, and shared responsibility.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id6270103a-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s1660d/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Requirement","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall ensure that the Service confers, to the maximum extent practicable, with urban Indian organizations in carrying out this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id6270103b-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/437/tV/s514"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–437, title V, § 514","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/148/tX/s10221/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–148, title X, § 10221(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-03-23"},"text":"Mar. 23, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/935"},"text":"124 Stat. 935","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id6270103c-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id6270103d-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id6270103e-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in subsec. (b), was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/437"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–437","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-09-30"},"text":"Sept. 30, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/1400"},"text":"90 Stat. 1400","children":[],"tail":", known as the Indian Health Care Improvement Act, which is classified principally to this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t25/s1601"},"text":"section 1601 of this title","children":[],"tail